div.p:
74. Vientiane 105 repeated Paris 16 London 17 Saigon 21 Bangkok Phnom Penh Unnumbered;
Supra.
Vientiane 108 repeated London 19 Paris 18 Saigon 22 Bangkok Phnom Penh Unnumbered.In telegram 108, July 18, the Embassy in Vientiane transmitted a report from the President of the Lao National Assembly, Pheng Pongsavan, through the British Ambassador, that Katay had obtained from Souvanna Phouma a pledge that as Prime Minister he would follow Katay’s policy. If Souvanna departed from Katay’s line, not only would his government fall, but he would be expelled from the Nationalist Party. (Department of State, Central Files, 751J.00/7–1857) We of course continue prefer Phoui to Souvanna but we recognize Phoui’s apparent lack of desire for job and probability Nationalists will retain mandate until they present Cabinet to Assembly, and accept your estimate we may have be prepared live with Souvanna.
